# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ Ω-FIELD-CELL  (canonical 72B 7-facet packed cell)

  § THESIS
    FieldCell ≡ canonical-Ω-field-cell-shape.
    ¬ "voxel" (too-render-biased)
    ¬ "tensor-element" (no-facet-discrimination)
    ¬ "ECS-component" (no-Σ-mask + no-Φ-handle + no-MERA-tier)
    ≡ 72B std430-aligned dense-cell carrying 7-facets : M, S, P, Φ, Σ-low
       (Λ + Ψ + Σ-high in sparse-overlays).

  § BYTE-LAYOUT  ‼ frozen via @layout(std430,soa) refinement
    ```text
    offset | bytes | facet | field
    -------+-------+-------+------------------------------------------
      0    |   8   |  M    | m_pga_or_region (1-bit tag + 63-bit id)
      8    |   4   |  S    | density (f32 ρ)
     12    |  12   |  S    | velocity (vec3<f32> u)
     24    |  12   |  S    | vorticity (vec3<f32> ω)
     36    |   4   |  S    | enthalpy (f32'pos H)
     40    |   8   |  S    | multivec_dynamics_lo (u64 packed bivector)
     48    |   8   |  P    | radiance_probe_lo (u64)
     56    |   8   |  P    | radiance_probe_hi (u64)
     64    |   8   | Φ + Σ | pattern_handle_lo (4B Φ) | sigma_low (4B Σ)
    -------+-------+-------+------------------------------------------
                72B total, 8-byte alignment, ¬ silent padding bytes
    ```
    invariant : core::mem::size_of::<FieldCell>() == 72
                core::mem::align_of::<FieldCell>() == 8
                ∀ multi-byte-field little-endian (std430-rule)
                ∀ byte semantically-occupied (Axiom-13 § II)

  § FACET-SEMANTICS
    M  Material-identity     1-bit-tag + 63-bit-id
                              tag=1 ⇒ PGA-handle (per-cell-individual material)
                              tag=0 ⇒ RegionID (table-lookup material-def)
                              ≡ supports both per-cell-bespoke + region-shared
    S  State-dynamics        density + velocity + vorticity + enthalpy +
                              multivec_dynamics_lo (packed PGA-grade-2 bivector)
                              ≡ continuum-mechanics-substrate per-cell
    P  Probe-radiance        16B radiance_probe_lo + radiance_probe_hi
                              ≡ stage-7 RC GI consumer ; per-cell SH-coeffs
    Φ  Pattern-handle        4B index into PhiTable (10000-D HDC hypervector)
                              ≡ semantic-cell-identity (creature/region/spell-tag)
                              PATTERN_HANDLE_NULL = 0 ⇒ unclaimed/air-cell
    Σ  Consent-low-cache     4B low-half of full SigmaMaskPacked (16B in overlay)
                              ≡ hot-path consent-bits cache
                              full mask consulted on slow-path mutation

  § OVERLAYS (sparse Morton-keyed)
    Λ-overlay (Symbol-Lattice)  : LambdaSimpleOverlay — sparse token-buckets
                                   ≡ event-tagged cells (footstep-here, spell-hit, dialogue-emit)
    Ψ-overlay (Wigner-magic)    : PsiOverlay — sparse f32 scalars
                                   ≡ Ψ-field "magic" non-classicality measure
    Σ-overlay (full-16B-mask)   : SigmaOverlay — sparse SigmaMaskPacked
                                   ≡ consent-claimed cells with non-default mask
                                   ~5% occupancy expected
    ‼ overlay-absent ⇒ default-value :
      Λ : empty-bucket (no events tagged)
      Ψ : 0.0 (classical-cell)
      Σ : SigmaMaskPacked::default_mask() (Default-Private)

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ SPARSE-MORTON-GRID  (canonical sparse-grid index)

  § THESIS
    Ω-field stored as sparse-Morton-keyed open-addressing hashtable.
    ¬ dense-array (M7 universe = 256m horizon @ 1cm = too-large dense)
    ¬ octree (cache-unfriendly, complex deletion, non-deterministic ordering)
    ≡ Morton-encoded 21-bit-per-axis Z-order curve →
       open-addressing hashtable with FxHash + linear-probing.

  § MORTON-KEY (63-bit payload + 1-bit sentinel)
    ```text
    bit 63       : reserved (0=valid, 1=sentinel/empty-slot)
    bits 0..=62  : interleaved Z-order
      bit 3i+0   : x[i]   for i in 0..=20
      bit 3i+1   : y[i]   for i in 0..=20
      bit 3i+2   : z[i]   for i in 0..=20
    ```
    axis-range : 0..=2^21-1 = 0..=2_097_151
    @ 0.125m cell-size : 262_144m per-axis (262km range — beyond M7 scope)
    @ 1cm fovea-tier   :  20_971m per-axis (20km — fine)

  § DETERMINISM-CONTRACT  ‼ load-bearing
    encoding W! bit-equal-across-hosts (replay-determinism)
    bit-spreading uses fixed-magic-number sequence (4-step)
    ¬ x86_64::_pdep_u64 (BMI2-PEXT/PDEP varies across hosts)
    ¬ NEON-equivalents that-may-vary
    ≡ pure-portable-software bit-spread = only-allowed-impl
    rationale : T11-D144 landmine — replay-bit-equality-across-hosts requires
                same bit-spread on Intel/AMD/Apple-Silicon

  § STORAGE-DISCIPLINE
    open-addressing hashtable (FxHash + linear-probing)
    load-factor : 0.75 default
    grow : 2× capacity, rehash-all (rare ; amortized O(1) insert)
    iter-order : Morton-key ascending (for replay-determinism on snapshot-walk)
    ≡ insertion-order does-NOT determine iter-order ; key-order does

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ MERA-PYRAMID  (4-tier hierarchical-LOD cascade)

  § THESIS
    MERA-style coarsening pyramid over the dense FieldCell-grid.
    Tier-0 = active-fovea ; Tier-3 = horizon-summary.
    ≡ enables LOD-aware-rendering + LOD-aware-physics + LOD-aware-AI
       without separate-mesh-LOD-asset-pipeline.

  § TIER-CASCADE
    Tier-0  fovea     1 cm  cells   (active-region-around-player)
    Tier-1  mid       4 cm  cells   (mid-range-detail)
    Tier-2  distant  16 cm  cells   (distant-but-visible)
    Tier-3  horizon  64 cm  cells   (summary-level-only)
    coarsening : 8-to-1 (2×2×2 fine-block → 1 coarse-cell)

  § COARSENING-SCHEME (stage-1 simple-averaging)
    density_T1 = mean(density_T0[8 cells])
    velocity_T1 = mean(velocity_T0)
    vorticity_T1 = mean(vorticity_T0)
    enthalpy_T1 = mean(enthalpy_T0)
    probe_lo / probe_hi : passthrough-from-representative-cell
    bivector_lo : passthrough
    sigma_consent_bits : intersection (most-restrictive consent)
    ≡ MERA-disentangler+isometry tensor-network DEFERRED to S12+ ;
       simple-average is canonical-fallback when trained-tensor-network
       not-available.

  § PER-TIER-STORAGE
    each tier = independent SparseMortonGrid<FieldCell>
    tier-0 : up-to-128-cells initial-capacity
    tier-1 : up-to-64-cells  initial-capacity
    tier-2 : up-to-32-cells  initial-capacity
    tier-3 : up-to-16-cells  initial-capacity
    tiers grow as world-occupancy increases.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ Σ-MASK-PER-CELL  (16B packed-bitmap consent-discipline)

  § THESIS
    every Ω-field-cell carries 16B std430-aligned packed-Σ-bitmap
    declaring : (a) op-class consent, (b) Sovereign-claim,
                (c) capacity-floor, (d) reversibility-scope, (e) audit-seq,
                (f) agency-state.
    ≡ cell-level enforcement of Axiom-4 AGENCY-INVARIANT.
    ≡ load-bearing surface that makes per-cell consent-threading
       possible without separate-per-op consent-dance.

  § BIT-LAYOUT  (16B = 128 bits, std430-aligned)
    ```text
     byte | bits     | field                  | type      | width
     -----+----------+------------------------+-----------+-------
      0   |  0..= 31 | consent_bits           | u32 flags |  32
      4   | 32..= 47 | sovereignty_handle     | u16       |  16
      6   | 48..= 63 | capacity_floor         | u16       |  16
      8   | 64..= 79 | reversibility_scope    | u16 enum  |  16
     10   | 80..= 95 | audit_seq              | u16       |  16
     12   | 96..=111 | agency_state           | u16 enum  |  16
     14   |112..=127 | reserved               | u16       |  16
    ```

  § CONSENT-BIT-FLAGS (32-bit op-class permission table)
    bit 0  Observe       : read-only inspection allowed
    bit 1  Modify        : in-place mutation allowed
    bit 2  Sample        : copy-out for derivative-computation allowed
    bit 3  Translate     : Travel-effect target allowed
    bit 4  Recrystallize : Crystallize-effect target allowed
    bit 5  Destroy       : remove-from-world allowed
    bit 6  Spawn         : add-new-cell-here allowed
    bit 7  Mark          : Λ-overlay token-attach allowed
    bits 8..=15 : reserved-for-future-op-classes
    bits 16..=31: reserved-for-extension (RESERVED-NONZERO ⇒ SIG0010 error)
    ‼ bit-positions FROZEN — reordering = ABI-break.

  § SOVEREIGN-HANDLE
    u16 handle into per-substrate Sovereign-table.
    SIGMA_SOVEREIGN_NULL = 0 = unclaimed/public
    nonzero ⇒ cell-claimed-by-Sovereign — MUST-MATCH ATTR_SOVEREIGN_AUTHORIZING
    on any-mutation. mismatch = SIG0004 compile-error.

  § REVERSIBILITY-SCOPE (u16 enum)
    Permanent      : N! revoke-allowed
    Session        : revoke-on-session-end allowed
    Substep        : revoke-this-tick allowed
    None           : default — fully-reversible, no-commit
    rule : Sovereign-claimed cell rejects Permanent unless
           Sovereign-itself authorizes (Σ-mask transition gated).

  § AGENCY-STATE (u16 enum)
    Active     : cell-may-be-mutated (default)
    Frozen     : ¬ cssl.fieldcell.destroy + ¬ cssl.fieldcell.modify
    Quiescent  : read-only this-step
    Halted     : kill-switch-target ; no-further-ops

  § DEFAULT-PRIVATE-MASK
    SigmaMaskPacked::default_mask() ≡ {
      consent_bits      : Observe-only (bit-0)
      sovereignty_handle: NULL
      capacity_floor    : 0
      reversibility_scope: None
      audit_seq         : 0
      agency_state      : Active
    }
    rationale : safest-default ; explicit-grant-required for any-write

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ ENFORCESΣATCELLTOUCHES-PASS  (F5 IFC compiler-pass)

  § THESIS
    cssl-mir::sigma_enforce::EnforcesΣAtCellTouches ≡ MIR-pass that
    structurally rejects any cell-touching op without Σ-mask discipline.
    closes 02_CSSL/00_LANGUAGE_CONTRACT § VI.D bullet
    "EnforcesΣAtCellTouches : every-Ω.Σ-touching-op type-checked".

  § OP-COVERAGE
    OP_FIELDCELL_READ
    OP_FIELDCELL_WRITE
    OP_FIELDCELL_MODIFY
    OP_FIELDCELL_DESTROY
    + any-op-w/-Travel-effect-row    (composes substrate-translation)
    + any-op-w/-Crystallize-effect-row (composes substrate-translation)

  § REQUIRED-ATTRIBUTES (per-op-site)
    ATTR_CONSENT_BITS              : declared Σ.consent-bits (u32 hex)
    ATTR_REQUIRED_BIT              : the SigmaCellOpKind::required_bit
    ATTR_SOVEREIGN_HANDLE          : cell's Sovereign-handle (u16)
    ATTR_SOVEREIGN_AUTHORIZING     : caller's act-as Sovereign
    ATTR_CAPACITY_FLOOR            : current floor (u16)
    ATTR_TARGET_CAPACITY_FLOOR     : post-op floor (u16) — MUST ≥ current
    ATTR_REVERSIBILITY_SCOPE       : current scope
    ATTR_TARGET_REVERSIBILITY_SCOPE: post-op scope
    ATTR_CELL_FACET                : agency-state ("frozen"/"active"/etc)

  § DIAGNOSTIC-CODES (stable — DO-NOT-renumber)
    SIG0001 : unguarded cell-write — no consent_bits attr
    SIG0002 : missing required_bit — declared bits but no required-bit
    SIG0003 : wrong consent-bit — required_bit ¬ in consent_bits mask
    SIG0004 : Sovereign mismatch — authorizing ≠ cell-handle on claimed cell
    SIG0005 : capacity-floor erosion — would-lower without authorizing
    SIG0006 : reversibility widening — Session→Permanent on claimed cell
    SIG0007 : Travel without Translate — Travel-row ¬ Translate-bit
    SIG0008 : Crystallize without Recrystallize — Crystallize-row ¬ Recrystallize
    SIG0009 : destroy when frozen — frozen-cell + destroy-op
    SIG0010 : reserved-nonzero — reserved-tail bits set (§7 INTEGRITY)

  § PASS-DISCIPLINE
    pass is MUTATION-FREE — surfaces violations through PassResult ;
    does-NOT rewrite the module.
    severity : ALL violations = Severity::Error
    canonical-pipeline halts on first error.
    each diagnostic message cites which-attribute-missing + what-pass-expected.

  § INTEGRATION-POINT (runtime double-check)
    cssl_substrate_omega_step::Phase5_AGENCY_VERIFY :
      runtime-tick double-check that compile-time-pass missed-nothing.
    ≡ defense-in-depth : compile-time + runtime both-enforce.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ OMEGA-STEP-6-PHASE-CONTRACT  (substrate-tick canonical-shape)

  § THESIS
    omega_step ≡ 6-phase canonical-tick over OmegaField.
    each phase is pure-w.r.t.-prior-phases (deterministic-replay-safe).
    phase-hooks are exposed as OmegaField::phase_<name>() methods.

  § THE-6-PHASES
    Phase-1  COLLAPSE      input-events + Σ-mask-resolution + observation collapse
                            ≡ T11-D113 hook = OmegaField::phase_collapse()
                            inputs : input-events, gaze-input, biometric-stream(banned-egress)
                            output : Σ-mask-updates, Λ-overlay tokens, fovea-budget
    Phase-2  PROPAGATE     ψ-PDE multi-rate solver (Wave-Unity)
                            ≡ T11-D114 hook = wave_solver_step (cssl-wave-solver)
                            sub-step 2b' : wave-unity ψ-PDE (full-substrate active-region)
                            sub-step 2c  : radiance cascades (read ψ-substrate as input)
                            implements : LBM + KAN-ODE + RC + Λ-stream + Ψ-flow
                            multi-rate : LIGHT 1ms / AUDIO 1ms / HEAT 100ms /
                                         SCENT 1s / MANA 250ms
    Phase-3  COMPOSE       operadic sheaf-glue (cell-to-cell consistency)
                            ≡ T11-D116 hook (renderer feeds back composed-fields)
                            ¬ consume Σ-claimed cells without authorizing
                            cross-cell coherence (Λ + Ψ + S facets reconciled)
    Phase-4  COHOMOLOGY    incremental persistent-homology (topology bookkeeping)
                            ≡ T11-D117 hook (physics-wave coupling-feedback)
                            tracks region-genus, cycles-emerge, holes-close
                            informs spell-magic-graph + creature-territory
    Phase-5  AGENCY-VERIFY consent-aggregate + reversibility-scope re-check
                            ≡ T11-D120 hook (gaze-collapse runs late here)
                            double-checks compile-time SIG0001-SIG0010 invariants
                            kill-switch-route : ω_halt() observed-and-honored here
    Phase-6  ENTROPY-BOOK  RG-flow + 9-conservation-laws bookkeeping
                            ≡ T11-D125 hook (audio-wave + procedural-anim)
                            ψ-norm conservation per-band
                            cross-band-coupling energy conservation
                            HEAT-band absorbs all losses (§XII.1)
                            audit-chain epoch advanced once-per-tick

  § PHASE-INVARIANTS
    P1-invariant : revoked-consent ⇒ corresponding-effects skip ; emit Audit
    P2-invariant : ψ-norm preserved per-band (modulo HEAT-absorption)
    P3-invariant : cross-cell coherence — no torn-state mid-phase
    P4-invariant : persistent-homology incremental ; total-recompute = bug
    P5-invariant : SIG-pass already-passed-at-compile ; runtime confirms
    P6-invariant : audit-append failure ⇒ panic (§§ 22 PRIME-DIRECTIVE)

  § FRAME-BUDGET-COMPOSITION (Quest-3 reference, 11.1 ms / 90 Hz)
    Phase-1 COLLAPSE      : 0.4 ms  (input-poll + Σ-resolve)
    Phase-2 PROPAGATE     : 4.0 ms  (LBM + RC + KAN-ODE)
    Phase-3 COMPOSE       : 1.5 ms  (sheaf-glue + cross-cell)
    Phase-4 COHOMOLOGY    : 0.8 ms  (persistent-homology)
    Phase-5 AGENCY-VERIFY : 0.3 ms  (Σ-runtime-check)
    Phase-6 ENTROPY-BOOK  : 0.4 ms  (RG + conservation-check + audit-append)
    sub-total            : 7.4 ms  (omega_step)
    ↳ leaves 3.7 ms for 12-stage signature-render-pipeline (§§ 32)

  § DETERMINISTIC-REPLAY-INVARIANTS  ‼ load-bearing
    invariant-1 : same(field-init, RNG-streams, input-events, dt)
                   ⇒ same(field-out, Σ-state, audit-deltas)
    invariant-2 : Morton-key encoding bit-equal-across-hosts (§ MORTON-KEY)
    invariant-3 : float-determinism via x86-64 SSE2 IEEE-754 round-to-nearest-even
    invariant-4 : N→N+1 epoch-transition is single-atomic ; no torn reads
    invariant-5 : @replay test (§§ 23) MUST pass on ALL {PureDet}-paths

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ WAVE-UNITY-INTEGRATION  (Phase-2 PROPAGATE solver)

  § THESIS
    Wave-Unity ≡ multi-rate complex-valued ψ-field solver advancing
    light + audio + heat + scent + mana as ONE complex field
    ψ(x,t) ∈ C sampled at different frequency bands.
    Cross-band coupling emerges from material impedance Z(λ, embedding) —
    NOT from authored-side-effects between-separate-engines.

  § BAND-CONFIG (5-band default per T11-D114)
    AUDIO_SUB_KHZ   : 0.5m cells, 1ms timestep, direct-amplitude LBM D3Q19
    LIGHT_RED       : 1cm cells, 1ms timestep, SVEA envelope
    LIGHT_GREEN     : 1cm cells, 1ms timestep, SVEA envelope
    LIGHT_BLUE      : 1cm cells, 1ms timestep, SVEA envelope
    LIGHT_NEAR_IR   : 1cm cells, 1ms timestep, SVEA envelope
    DEFERRED : HEAT (100ms) , SCENT (1s) , MANA (250ms)
    generic : WaveField<C> const-generic over band-count

  § SOLVER-TYPE
    EXPLICIT  : D3Q19 LBM stream + collide for AUDIO band (Complex<f32>)
    IMEX      : implicit-stiff back-Euler relaxation for LIGHT bands ;
                explicit for AUDIO ; adaptive Δt with KAN-predicted-stability

  § BOUNDARY-CONDITIONS
    SDF-Robin-BC over bc::SdfQuery trait
    KAN-impedance Z(λ, embedding) via KanMaterial::physics_impedance
    ≡ wall-reflectivity emerges from learned material-table
    ≡ no separate-render-vs-physics material authoring

  § CROSS-BAND-COUPLING (§XI verbatim)
    LIGHT→AUDIO  : shimmer (asymmetric, allowed)
    AUDIO→MAGIC  : Λ-overlay tag-emit (allowed)
    MAGIC→AUDIO  : emission (allowed)
    MAGIC→LIGHT  : emission (allowed)
    LIGHT→MANA   : 0  ‼ STRICT-ZERO-ENFORCED
    AUDIO→MANA   : 0  ‼ STRICT-ZERO-ENFORCED

  § CONSERVATION (Phase-6 ENTROPY-BOOK consumer)
    ψ-norm preservation per-band
    cross-band-coupling energy conservation
    HEAT-band absorbs all losses (§XII.1)
    9 conservation rows ∀ tick ; row-violations = panic + audit-entry

  § REPLAY-DETERMINISM
    bit-equal across-runs given same (band-init, dt, BCs, KAN-weights)
    KAN-stability-Kan : MockStabilityKan stage-1, real KAN trained @ S12+

